author: @pperez1224
text: Quotient rule : d/dx(U(x)/V(x)) = U(x)' V(x) - U(x) V'(x) / V(x)^2   , in our case , U is U (x,y,z ) so we use partial derivatives 3 variables : setosa , versicolor and virginica d( E(x) / E(x)+Constant ) is the first equation we derive. Constant= E(versicolor)+E(virginica ). With clever identifications , Josh has a simple final formulae :)
